The article discusses the importance of small businesses in the United States and the challenges they faced during the COVID-19 pandemic. It highlights the resilience and determination of small business owners and workers who adapted to sudden changes and supported their communities. The article mentions the economic relief provided by the American Rescue Plan, including loans and support for small businesses, especially those in the hardest-hit industries. It also mentions efforts to vaccinate the population, with a focus on helping small businesses reopen and creating a tax credit for employees to get vaccinated. The article emphasizes the commitment to supporting underserved small businesses, including those owned by veterans, women, and people of color. It mentions efforts to strengthen contracting programs for underserved small businesses to boost job opportunities and economic prosperity. The article concludes by recognizing the contributions of small businesses and proclaiming September 12 to September 18 as National Small Business Week.